ns2:Book05f5e2d7-b5bb-4174-8ab7-e2a33c90d681 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Emilie Leduc" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54472" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Groundwood_Books ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Every month of the year is special, and a child takes readers through them all, starting with January. Each two-page spread covers a month and includes a short, non-rhyming poem that tells what that month means to the child, as well as an accompanying full-page illustration. \r
\r
Simple, clear and evocative language creates unique observations about the seasons. In November, “the snow drifts everywhere. But beneath my feet lie hidden treasures in all the colours of the rainbow.” All months are equal to the child, who professes her adoration 12 times: “I love the month of August and the nice warm sand.” \r
\r
The illustrations portray a sweet-faced child, who could be any gender, with rosy cheeks and dark emotive eyes. Images range in colour to reflect the changing seasons in a soft wash of watercolour. Sometimes they zoom in on the main character, such as when the child is swimming, and sometimes they zoom out, such as when the child is zipping around on a bike. The child isn’t the only one experiencing the months. Readers can also follow Clementine, who participates as much as a cat can, in the child’s monthly activities.""" ;
    ns2:title "All Year Round" ;
