    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=52995" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2001"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "NorthSouth Books"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """A cat and a dog live in the same house, but clearly do not like each other. The two fight constantly, over treats and places to sleep. And yet, when a situation arises where they truly need one another, they discover that they do have some common ground after all and the adversaries become friends. \r
Sentences are spread over several pages, describing the animosity between the two animals. Through the text, we hearsee two voices: “Clumsy dog” and “Hsss!” are written near the cat to show its thoughts; “Fussy cat” and “Grrr!” are written beside the dog. \r
The two creatures are drawn in clearly different (though complementary, it must be noted) colours, with the cat in blue and the dog in orange. Each animal occupies an opposite page, further emphasizing their differences, until the final pages when they have developed a bond and are seen together.\r
Readers may make connections to their own experiences: Why they don’t get along with some people? And more importantly, what might they have in common?""" ;
