    ns2:datePublished "2012"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:MacMilan ;
    ns2:reviewBody """The award-winning Madeleine L’Engle novel is transformed and honoured in this graphic novel rendition. Meg and her brother are called upon to save their scientist father who is lost in a sinister universe. They travel on a rescue mission through time with the assistance of three ancient and unusual wise women. Accompanied by a new friend with uncanny powers, Meg discovers that sometimes one’s greatest weakness is one’s truest strength, and is able to rescue her family from danger.\r
Staying true to the original by preserving every scene and nearly all of its dialogue, the adventure will keep readers riveted. Language is packed with wisdom and humanity. Meg’s mother explains: “One thing I’ve learned is that you don’t have to understand things for them to be.”\r
The graphics, rendered in a minimalistic white, blue and black palette, manage to navigate the “tessering” through dimensions of time and space, capturing both mathematical concepts and human details. Close-ups are used to great effect to capture human emotion, as are wordless sequences that reflect the numinous qualities of the original text.\r
Self-discovery, resilience and belief are at the heart of this epic tale, as is the ability to be transformed by what happens to one, no matter how challenging.""" ;
