    ns2:datePublished "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Greenwillow Books – HarperCollins Publishers"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This picture book is a step-by-step description of how flowers grow. Readers are implicated from the moment the seeds are planted, and they are even invited to activate the sun and rain: “Tap the cloud and wish for rain. Clap to bring the sun again.” The pattern cycles through day and night as the plants grow and the flowers open up, attracting—“Bzzzzzzzz!”—pollinators. The cycle of growth even extends to soil aeration (readers are invited to spot the worm), and reseeding, emphasizing that, although humans may have a hand in planting flowers, nature itself works to complete the process. The rhyming couplets and simple vocabulary are playful enough to make learning about plant growth, pollination, and seeding attractive and fun. The book concludes with more detailed information on how to plant zinnias. \r
\r
Collages combine colour, texture and layers to create an inviting garden. The white background, which becomes deep indigo at night, is a blank canvas for the green sprouts and the red, purple and orange flowers that eventually bloom. The sun and clouds peek out of the top of the page, while various garden insects are fun for young readers to spot. The final pages—“Oh, look! There’s magic everywhere!”—are full of pollinators, including a hummingbird, bees and different butterflies.""" ;
    ns2:title "Plant the Tiny Seed" ;
