    ns2:reviewBody """Explore the world of “once upon a time” in this engaging compilation of 10 beloved princess stories from Cinderella to Sleeping Beauty to The Princess and the Pea. Marvel over bright, watercolour paintings as they partner with lively poetic retellings of princesses who dance, dream, cross the sea, tame a beast, lose a shoe, kiss a frog, etc. The fun doesn’t stop there. Something is hiding on every page. Can you find it?\r
Told in rhyme, each fairy tale incorporates the basic elements of the original, using rich, accessible language: “From a seed of barleycorn,Thumbelina would be born.” The poems appear within a decorative border topped with a large, colourful header.\r
Several different cultures are depicted throughout the book, in spreads that draw readers in and vividly dramatize the stories. A seek-and-find feature invites readers to try to locate objects hidden in the artwork. (An italicized list appears underneath each poem.)\r
The interactivity, enticing watercolours and comfortable familiarity of the stories may encourage readers to discover poetry with fresh ears and eyes as well.""" ;
