    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This companion text to Will Grayson, Will Grayson is a musical written by the beloved giant hero, Tiny Cooper. Tiny takes centre stage in this hilarious, inventive and outrageous musical extravaganza about gay identity, gender stereotypes, friendships, first love and breakups.\r
With song titles like: “OH! What a Big Gay Baby!” and “Parade of Ex-boyfriends” and lyrics such as “I was born this way,big-boned and happily gay.I was born this way,right here in the U. S. of A.,” this captivating and unapologetic text confronts self-esteem issues, using humour to look at the joys and difficulties of being a gay teen.\r
The musical follows Tiny from 0-16, growing up in his Chicago family, with football as religion, meeting his best friend in little league, coming out as gay and going through a string of 18 exes, before meeting “The Ghost of Oscar Wilde.”\r
There is a wonderful editorial voice of Tiny himself infused throughout the stage directions that he orchestrates down to the last detail: “A note on the spotlight: It should be clear from the very beginning that this is Tiny’s special place . . . there are those of us who draw our power from those electric moments when everyone is watching.”\r
This combination of speech, stage directions and song lyrics will have readers hooked on Tiny Cooper.""" ;
