ns2:Book2c206d45-5596-4fb0-910f-506f5a7e53d2 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Natalie Mae" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=56675" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Razorbill – Penguin Random House"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This fantasy novel about a young woman who is in the wrong place at the wrong time shows the value of kindness and resourcefulness. There is to be a Crossing in the magical kingdom of Orkena, a race across the desert by the three potential heirs to the throne in order to pick a ruler. Kasta is the oldest brother, but he is cruel; Jet, the illegitimate second brother, wants nothing to do with the throne; and Sakira, the youngest, is something of a party girl. Zahru, the novel’s protagonist, and her best friend sneak into the palace festivities, but things go awry and Zahru ends up being chosen as a companion for the royal quest, then marked as the human sacrifice that traditionally takes place at its conclusion. Through her wit and her magic—Zahru is a Whisperer, which means she can speak with animals—Zahru manages to escape, outwit Kasta, and convince Jet that he must accept the responsibilities of leadership. Her dominant strength is kindness, though, as she is told by the ancient Speaker: “kindness is like a poison. Sometimes it takes time to work.”\r
\r
The first-person point of view shows a relatable, somewhat self-deprecating young woman whose priorities are looking after her aging father and maintaining her relationship with her best friend even after the two of them go their separate ways upon completing their magic training. The secondary characters, including the three royal siblings and their assorted magical aides-de-camps, are compelling, distinct and nuanced, with blurred, complex combinations of good and evil. The world creation is fun and thorough, and some choices, such as the people's blind faith in magic and in the will of the high priests, echo real-life social concerns. The book ends with the beginning of a war, which creates suspense for a subsequent installment.""" ;
