    ns2:datePublished "2014"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Groundwood_Books ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Based on the author’s childhood memories of her father’s life as a tailor, this is the heartwarming tale of Mr. Frank’s last day on the job, when an order comes in for the most important outfit of his career. What could it be? And who is the mysterious client? Follow him on the eve of his retirement as he tries to decide what design, style and fabric he will use for this very special item.\r
The understated text of this charming read-aloud subtly builds suspense until the very end when readers discover that the outfit is none other than a superhero costume for the tailor’s very special grandson.\r
Double spreads of graphite and mixed media illustrations convey an old-world feel, and evoke the textiles and period detail of the fashions Mr. Frank has been “measuring, cutting, stitching, sewing, mending and pressing” throughout his 60-year career.\r
This is a story to be shared inter-generationally, both for its visual overview of fashion trends through time and for its warm depiction of the love between a grandfather and grandson.""" ;
