ns2:Book4155a17b-2a83-4c76-b7b7-a3f77a715a0e a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Marine Leavitt" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54832" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2012"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Groundwood_Books ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This powerful free verse novel is recommended for mature students. It touches on street life for women and girls in Downtown Eastside Vancouver. With pathos, insight and wit, 16-year-old Angel’s voice speaks for this vulnerable sector, victimized by criminals, citizens and the law: “I saw how every time I was only in the man’s wishes, not a real girl, just a guess, a question, a story he made up—” \r
When Angel decides to quit the “candy” that pimp Call has been feeding her, she reflects on her past home life, and her seduction by Call. The dangers of street life are reflected in the theme of missing women; Angel’s friend Serena is the latest: “Widow said, I got a bad feeling about that van… everyone on the street is saying there’s a killer but the police say no.” \r
\r
The artistry of the language mitigates the grim aspects of this important story. Opportunities abound for discussion about social justice, gender equality and family relationships. A running theme on Milton’s Paradise Lost, introduced to Angel by “John the john,” provides further insight into sexism, while offering literary enrichment: “He said, Milton added 630 words to our vocabulary. Before Milton there was no fragrance or lovelorn, no debauchery or stunning, no unprincipled.” \r
\r
The stakes are raised when 11-year-old Melli joins Angel as Call’s prisoner, and a crooked cop and pedophile dentist emerge as Call’s allies. In a satisfying finish, Angel launches a counter-attack on their victimizers, saving Melli and freeing herself: “I bought my own copy of paradise lost… and turned… to the very last book, book twelve, and nobody could stop me.” \r
\r
An author’s note provides background information and honours the missing and murdered women of Downtown Eastside Vancouver.""" ;
