ns2:Book47cf6271-e0ba-416d-8d78-b52fe442c723 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Dennis Lee" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=52250" ;
    ns2:datePublished "1977"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:HarperCollins ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This collection of 42 children’s poems was released in the 1970s, but the silly and down-to-earth rhymes continue to make it an excellent introduction to poetry for children.\r
Poet Dennis Lee, who also authored the classic children’s poetry book Alligator Pie, uses playful and cheeky imagery that children can relate to, making poetry easily accessible to young readers. The poems explore the everyday moments of a child’s world, from the wonders of being age five to the struggles of learning to dress oneself. Lee takes on many different perspectives, such as that of a fly caught in a bowl of soup, which will make children curious about even the most mundane parts of the world around them.\r
Canadian geography also figures prominently throughout the poems, giving them a distinctly Canadian flavour and opening children’s minds to the country’s wonderful diversity. The book retains the original illustrations from the 1970s, evoking the artwork of that time through prints that often use only one colour, and bringing to mind the illustrations of Maurice Sendak.\r
The short verses, rhyming words and rapid rhythm of the poems invite children and adults alike to enjoy chanting the poems aloud.""" ;
    ns2:title "Garbage Delight" ;
