ns2:Book54bd9997-bdac-43db-89e9-ae1201936894 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Isabel Minhós Martins" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=53375" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2015"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Enchanted Lion Books"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“Every time a second crosses the world… millions of things happen, here, there, everywhere.” So begins this journey around the world in 23 double-page spreads, with 23 stories of time frozen at the same unique moment. In the Baltic Sea, a heavily laden cargo boat is tossed by storm waves. Meanwhile, in Mexico City, a traffic jam frustrates the driver of a car. A volcano erupts in Papua New Guinea.\r
This oversized volume uses striking imagery in vivid matte colours to tell its story of lightning quick international time travel. Thin paper strips, cut from a document, feature the one or two sentences per page. The flat graphic art uses geometric shapes and creates a sense of continuity between the countries, emphasizing our interconnectedness no matter where we are on earth.\r
Language is simple, but the accumulation of small events evokes a feeling of poetic wonderment at what might be going on around the world at any given moment. “A girl hurries home from school” in a northern snowy landscape. In the bustle of Tokyo’s rush hour, “a man sits down to rest … (for just one second, he tells himself)” and more dramatically, “A house is demolished (it takes no more than a second).”\r
A map at the back of the book pinpoints the 23 locations.""" ;
