ns2:Book65453c1a-6ab2-4d50-9279-830b3bf69d17 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Suzy Lee" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=55603" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2010"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Seven Footer Press"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This evocative wordless picture book uses reflected and symmetrical images in this tale of friendship, found and lost, about a little girl who discovers her mirror-self. \r
Minimal layouts on blank pages use the book-gutter as a line of symmetry, creating mirror-image spreads that depict loneliness, discovery and timidity, followed by mutuality and play. A masterful use of charcoal line and smudge effects combine with ink fills to make lively and expressive images of a child, her reflection and the Rorschach-like splotches that represent the energy of the two figures’ games. \r
The plot offers opportunities for storytelling and prediction when, at the height of joyful accord, girl and reflection meld into the gutter—leaving nothing but two blank pages. When they re-emerge, the figures are symmetrical: now they mimic (as opposed to reflect) each other. Did they cross paths in the gutter, to emerge on the other side? Soon they are each doing their own thing. \r
Challenging aspects of friendship are conveyed as the girls sulk and glare across the gutter-divide. In frustration, one reaches out to push, and the mirror shatters. A spooky final image recalls the first—a child huddled and alone. Except now, the figure is a perfect reflection of the first: who was in the mirror, and who remains?""" ;
    ns2:title "Mirror" ;
    ns1:isCoupDeCoeur false ;
    ns1:keyword "Picture book",
        "feelings",
        "imagination",
        "wordless book" .

ns2:Book654b64a6-a43e-497d-9a1a-05c518bca3d0 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Edmond Géraldine d'après Rostand Maincent" ;
