ns2:Book66805c0c-6c95-42bb-ab7e-264487765510 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Danielle Marcotte" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=55571" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2016"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Owlkids ;
    ns2:reviewBody """A heartwarming account of one young boy’s exploration of reading in his family. An early reader, he discovers how this wondrous activity brings everything around him to life. “I know how to turn pages, name pictures, and sound out words. I can read now. Like the big kids!” \r
Narrated by the boy, the story starts at home and moves out into the world, staying close to family as he uncovers all the marvelous things reading unlocks. Not only stories, but cooking, playing music, the weather, facial expressions, the future, timetables and thermometers. The philosophical, matter-of-fact voice is inviting and brings the reader into his experience: “Thanks to books, I find balance, I climb high, I follow new roads, and I move forward.” \r
Mixed-media illustrations in bright colours combine digital collage, paint, crayon and pencil. Patterns and colours are used effectively, making the visual world lively and engaging. Artwork subtly brings whimsy and imagination to the everyday: Vegetables float out of a cookbook in Uncle’s kitchen, sea monsters hug the bath as the boy reads an adventure book, and Grandma floats up to the clouds on the drift of a good story. \r
Comforting and down-to-earth, the familiar is nicely blended with the imaginative to create a work that will inspire even the reluctant reader to dive in.""" ;
