ns2:Book701ad5be-3b0c-4a6a-b3b7-708699f1fd03 a ns2:Book ;
    ns2:author "Adam Lehrhaupt" ;
    ns2:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=52161" ;
    ns2:datePublished "2013"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Simon___Schuster ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This book will engage beginner readers by starting with a suggestion they’ll delight in refusing: “Maybe you should put this book back. You don’t want to let the monkeys out.” \r
By addressing children directly and “reacting” to their responses, the language expertly entices them into the act of reading. “Why did you turn the page? Didn’t you see the warning?” The narration is both familiar and humorous in its conversational tone: “Oh no. Now you’ve done it.”\r
Illustrations offer detailed and artistic representations in painterly textures and tones. The unleashed monkeys are portrayed in a range of recognizable species. While the text describes their mess, young readers may note they are painting their own background illustration. By turning more pages, children unleash toucans and, finally, a terrifying alligator. Luckily, clever youngsters can use the book to trap them all back inside—by turning a few more pages. \r
Fun, expressive and an absolute joy to read aloud, this book belongs in any beginner reading library.""" ;
