    ns2:datePublished "2018"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Orca ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“They were heading straight for our building. They were coming for us.” Clear language, taut sentence structure, action, romance and a tropical location are featured in this snappy mystery.\r
Told in the voice of Tom who is thrilled to be on the Mayan Riviera with his long-distance girlfriend Kat and her father, FBI agent Mike, the story bolts from the starting gate: “A spear sliced the air—an inch from my face! . . . The jungle swallowed me.” A carefully constructed plot offers many suspicious—sometimes sinister—characters: on the plane, among the guests at their fancy resort, as well as among the crooked cops that Mike’s local police connection warns them about.\r
The fun setting includes snorkeling dives, sea turtles and a special camaraderie with the marina staff since Tom’s family runs a marina on the Canadian side of the Detroit River: “Our captain had two gold teeth right in the middle of his smile. His name was equally cool. ‘I am called Crispy Bacon,’ he said. I couldn’t wait to tell Dad. He’d love that.”\r
But the holiday takes a dark turn when Mike is mysteriously shot and a police officer’s daughter is kidnapped. While Kat is busy at the hospital with her father, Tom accidentally locates the little girl and frees her. This leads to a chase through Mayan ruins, the unmasking of the villain and the threat of death on the open sea—before rescue comes in a most unexpected form. Like all the best action-mystery-romances, this one ends with a kiss, as Kat says, “I feel like I need a whole new vacation.”""" ;
