    ns2:datePublished "2014"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Simon___Schuster ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“Breathe, little whale! Play all day, and swim, and swim, and swim.”\r
Alongside a young beluga, readers explore the ocean and its array of sea life, from puffins to squid, zipping around the waters. Very few words, spoken in the imperative voice, encourage the young white whale to travel the ocean world. Meanwhile, the reader has the time and space to closely examine the visual context.\r
Digital illustrations with friendly, cartoonish faces bring the sea to life, and the various mammals and fish inspire an awe of nature. The night-time scene of the bottom of the ocean is especially enchanting, complete with a sunken ship and twinkling air bubbles in the place of stars.\r
The text has a repetitive, meditative quality that may be used to help readers relax or get ready for bed, or perhaps even address the topics of anxiety and wellness.\r
Just like in the life of humans, there is friendship and adventure, including a looming polar bear who is ultimately avoided. A message of security wraps up the voyage: “Most of all, love and be loved. Dream big. Sleep deep tonight. Breathe.”""" ;
