    ns2:publisher "Wisdom Tales"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """The brief language in this book offers young readers a glimpse into the ways people worship around the world.\r
“People pray when they are happy, giving thanks. And people pray when they are sad, seeking peace.” Through the lens of prayer, children will encounter the names of different religions (Buddhist, Sikh, Shinto), different places of worship (“temples, churches, or mosques, while others pray outside”), as well as tools and methods for praying (“books, beads, or candles . . . singing and dancing . . . quiet and still”).\r
Defined line and rich colour create realistic, large-size scenes such as people face- and hand-washing in a mosque courtyard, and a river baptism. Readers will see Maasai, jumping beneath the spreading branches of a tree; they’ll see Jews, pressing close to a stone wall. There are children learning the Quran, while others kneel before an image of Mary.\r
Both language and illustrations invite questions and discussion. Helpful back material offers summaries of the 10 religions discussed and notes for each illustration. While educating youngsters on the diversity of religions around us, this book emphasizes the commonality of all: “Everyone Prays!”""" ;
