    ns2:datePublished "1989"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Simon___Schuster ;
    ns2:reviewBody """This crew of colourful lower-case alphabet letters are a rambunctious bunch. They all race each other up a coconut tree in this lively introduction to the alphabet. But chaos ensues when the tree becomes overloaded with letters: “H is tangled up with I . . . L is knotted like a tie.” \r
Characters like black-eyed P and loose-tooth T will appeal to young readers. Text is rhyming and rhythmic, using expressive vocabulary and onomatopoeia to capture the fun being had by the letters as they race, tumble, giggle and play. The simple, repetitive style of the verse (“M is looped. N is stooped”) and refrain (“Chicka chicka boom boom!Will there be enough room?”) lends itself well to participatory chanting during a class read-aloud. The illustrations are done in bright, almost neon colours, predominantly created from straight lines and geometric forms. \r
Children will have so much fun with this story that they will hardly notice they are learning the letters of the alphabet.""" ;
