    ns2:datePublished "2013"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Peachtree Publishers"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Lion is downright mean to all the animals. He gives Buffalo a wedgie, sticks a silly note on Zebra’s back and steals hyena’s lunch monkey! When they can’t take it anymore, they post an ad asking for help. One by one, Bear, Moose and Tiger arrive in to take on the big bully, but none are any match for his prowess and skill. Who could have predicted that the last to arrive on the scene, a small rabbit, would be the one to finally outsmart him?\r
Filled with sly wit—the opening page shows a pair of stat cards ranking Lion and Rabbit’s meanness and brains on a scale of one to ten—this read-aloud features stylized kid-friendly illustrations that are digitized, then coloured to capture the particular expressions and personalities of each animal.\r
Addressing a sensitive topic without talking down to readers, the story involves a surprise twist that will draw a chuckle as it focuses on the importance of cooperation to solve the problem of bullying.""" ;
