    ns2:datePublished "2018"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Orca ;
    ns2:reviewBody """“Ten toucans drawing plansNine moles digging holes.” In this colourful board book, young readers learn how to count back from ten thanks to an industrious and diverse crew of animals who work together to build a house “… fit for a mouse!” Fun to read aloud, the text spills forward in rhymes, smooth as the cement laid down by “eight crabs pouring slabs.”\r
Numerals are paired with the written-out numbers (“7 Seven owls using trowels”) in this visually engaging learning tool. Each scene is set against a graph-paper backdrop, hinting at careful planning, while vibrant mixed media illustrations, rendered with pencils, pencil crayon, gouache, photographs and digital colouring, enliven the building process.\r
The project advances quickly thanks to the combined efforts of the critters, demonstrating the benefits of friendly collaboration. Before long, “Three foxes” are seen “moving boxes” while “Two bees” are shown shaking hands, “cutting keys.” It’s already time for the mouse to move in.\r
But that’s not all! A surprise ending sends the reader right back to the beginning: “Psst … did you find the heart hidden on each page?” the narrator cleverly whispers on the final spread. As the reader returns for another round, this time seeking the hearts hidden in each drawing, it becomes clear that the mouse’s cozy new house, a surprise gift from the critters, is a true labour of love.""" ;
