    ns2:datePublished "2012"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Greystone Books"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Based on Rick Hansen's Man in Motion World Tour, this is the inspiring story of a Canadian youth whose dream of creating an inclusive, accessible world and of finding a cure for spinal cord injuries took him on a 43 000-kilometre journey that made history in 1985.\r
Full-page colour illustrations and a compelling text, in the form of journal entries, depict the ups and downs of his travels by wheelchair through 34 countries including the US, Europe, Australia, China and the Middle East, and back again through the ten provinces of Canada, to raise money and increase public awareness for his cause. Along the way, he meets many people, like Jack, who has a similar injury, and Lin, a Chinese girl whose dreams of being a ballerina and leaping gracefully over a wall as high as the Great Wall of China provoke Rick's response to her that “There are no walls in life you can't climb.”\r
The book includes a section at the end containing little-known facts about the tour (e.g. 160 wheelchair tires wore out), and a note from Rick Hansen inviting readers to do whatever they can to make a difference in the world.""" ;
