    ns2:datePublished "2011"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher ns2:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns2:reviewBody """Located in a crumbling, futuristic Los Angeles, the Republic of America is run by a military dictatorship that seeks to keep order against the rebel Patriots and a plague that is ransacking the poorer districts of the city. Told in alternating chapters by two very different teen wonders, June and Day, their stories converge into one love story that has them fighting for their lives.\r
June, the Republic’s best-loved prodigy, got a perfect score on her Trial, the exam that all 10-year-olds must pass to determine their ranking in society. She is about to graduate from a top University and take up a leadership position fighting for the military.\r
Day is a poor boy from the wrong side of the tracks, trying to save his family from the Plague, with inside information about the reality of June’s beloved Republic. “I’m not the most dangerous criminal in the country, but the most wanted.”\r
This action thriller uses incisive and quick-paced plotting to reveal conspiracies and uncover truths that are hard for its characters to hear. The two voices are written in an authentic first-person teenager style that grips the reader, pulling them into their very divergent realities, until it becomes clear that, surprisingly, they are on the same side.""" ;
