    ns2:publisher ns2:Kids_Can_Press ;
    ns2:reviewBody """The nature of matter, in all its changing forms, is outlined in this useful beginning science book. Sections such as “Matter around you,” “What’s a liquid?” and ”Freezing and melting” offer brief definitions in large type and clear language.\r
The language leads young readers to search the illustrations for examples. Sections such as “Pour it in!”, “Cool it!” and “Paint with salt!” describe simple science experiments for kids to put the principles in action.\r
Full-page illustrations are bright and cheery, with a graphic cartoon-like edge. Children will connect with the individualized kid-characters, whether they are drinking soda at the diner, walking the dog or conducting the experiments. Talking animals offer sidebar information.\r
Back material includes a parentteacher guide with ideas for further discussion and exploration, as well as a brief glossary and index.\r
Young readers wanting to explore and have fun in their science investigations need look no further than this book.""" ;
