    ns2:datePublished "2013"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns2:publisher "Amazon"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:reviewBody """When Kitty Cat’s mother tells him it’s time for school, the little cat is very excited to greet the day and all the fun it promises. His teacher is “so cool”!\r
Each page features rhyming couplets structured as a call and answer between Kitty Cat and his teacher (or, on the way to school, his mother). The segments explore common early-childhood school activities, including art, recess, show and tell, counting and naptime. In each one, the anthropomorphized feline protagonist displays unbridled enthusiasm at what is suggested: When the teacher announces that it’s snack time, for example, (“Kitty Cat, Kitty Cat, time to have a treat”), Kitty Cat gushes, “Yum yum, Teacher, I always like to eat.”\r
The full-page pencil and watercolour drawings are representative but light-hearted, showing the kitten school chums singing, skipping rope or sleeping all curled up in a pile, often with a playful background featuring a sweet recurring mouse interloper.\r
At school, learning is fun. The pupils are well-surrounded and well-loved. It’s no wonder that at the end of the day, Kitty Cat exclaims, “I had SO MUCH FUN!”""" ;
